ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org}


[These figures differ from those reported in the most recent MMWR update
(see: West Nile virus surveillance 2001 - USA (34) 20011130.2914). The MMWR
update states that as of 20 Nov 2201, a total of 48 human cases of WNV
encephalitis or meningitis have been reported in New York (12), Florida
(10), New Jersey (7), Connecticut (6), Maryland (6), Pennsylvania (3),
Massachusetts (2), Georgia (1), and Louisiana (1). Among these 48 cases, 27
(56 per cent) were males (median age 70 years; range: 36 to 90); dates of
illness onset ranged from 13 Jul to 15 Oct 2001; and 5 patients (10 per
cent) died. The third case of WNV infection in Massachusetts reported above
brings the total number of human cases to at least 49. - Mod.CP
